pam_access

This module manages pam_access entries stored in /etc/security/access.conf.  It
requires Augeas >= 0.8.0.

Sample usage:

  class {
    'pam_access':
      exec => true;
  }

  pam_access::entry {
    'mailman-cron':
      user   => 'mailman',
      origin => 'cron';
    'root-localonly':
      permission => '-',
      user       => 'root',
      origin     => 'ALL EXCEPT LOCAL';
    'lusers-revoke-access':
      create => false,
      user   => 'lusers',
      group  => true;
  }

Changes:

0.0.2 - Specify `incl` and `lens` parameters to augeas resources for
        performance improvement.

0.0.1 - Initial release.
